She flipped to a blank page and wrote down the date. Beneath it, she wrote "11.5.648–13.12.648".
"Are you reviving an old memory?" asked Ivory and looked at the old notebook. Kari nodded. "Do you think they'll let you out for Christmas? There are only a few days left."
Kari tapped twice on the lantern. "No," as Ivory had suspected. The Ice King never let Kari out, as he considered her a "blemish." She was born deaf and was the only daughter in the family, her siblings were all boys.
Something similar applied to Ivory as well. When Ivory came out as nonbinary, it seemed as if the world changed too. As punishment for this difference, Ivory received tasks that mostly required being alone.
In addition, Ivory was also forced to serve the princess. However, it didn't bother Ivory much, since Ivory gained a friend.
"You're going to have a birthday soon, right?" asked Ivory, as she remembered that the princess had a birthday in a few days. Kari nodded with a sad flicker in her bright blue eyes.
"Would you like to celebrate your birthday?" asked Ivory, thinking about the last time the princess had answered this question.
"No," tapped Kari. Ivory knew that this was a difficult topic for her. Her birthday was the day she was locked in this room and her mother was banished. Ivory had been a baby at that time, but she remembered how upset the servants and the city's residents had been. Ivory had heard that Eirwen was a popular queen. And strangely enough, she could also predict things that then actually happened.
"Well, what would you like to do?" asked Ivory. Kari looked excitedly at Ivory. She held a piece of paper in her hand. On it was written:
15 x 15 cm canvas
White, various shades of blue
Bristle brushes in six different sizes
Easel
„These things should I get for you?“, Ivory addressed the quiet princess, whose braids swung back and forth from her vigorous knocking. „Yes?“ Ivory chuckled softly. The usually reserved princess showed so much enthusiasm. It was the first time she had asked for something that had nothing to do with books and came from outside her room.
„Okay! See you later?“, Ivory asked, stood up and slung herself through the chaos of papers and notebooks.
Kari nodded, turned back to her notes, and wrapped herself in her bed sheet.
Ivory left the room, relieved that the princess had finally stepped out of her comfort zone and asked for things beyond her reach, like malachite.
Ivory ran through the corridors again and tried to ignore the whispers of the servants.
„I heard that she is supposed to be possessed by Queen Eirwen and therefore keeps going into this room again and again.“
„I heard that she eats children in this room.“
“She looks like a man, that's not normal, is it?”
Ivory covered her ears because she couldn't ignore the chatter and continued on. The room of the royal painter was located in the east wing behind the second door on the left side.
Ivory approached the door, which was decorated as artfully as Karis door. On it was the White Dragon, one of the six original dragons said to have created Frostfell. For a history-loving painter, the White Dragon on the door certainly made sense.
Ivory opened the door and expected the usual mess. Paint splatters everywhere, brushes and paper scattered throughout the room, easels covering every inch of the wall. Unexpectedly, however, a different scene unfolded. The entire room was clean, and in front of a red velvet background stood a chair. On the chair sat Crown Prince Aquilo, who was being portrayed.
“Good morning, Ivory! Would you like to watch as your future king is portrayed?” asked Aquilo and winked at Ivory.
"Excuse me, little prince," said Ivory, largely ignoring him and gathering the things the quiet princess wished for. "I'm only here to get the art supplies."
"My little girl wants to go already?" asked Aquilo. "But I want you to stay!"
"I don't want to," said Ivory. Ivory found the art supplies on the list and placed them in a box. "Besides, I'm not a girl."
However, the prince had a different opinion. "Oh sweetie, that's just a phase! As you get older, you'll grow out of it!" he said unclearly.
"I have to go," said Ivory and felt uncomfortable because of the prince's answer. Ivory remembered all the ugly comments he and others had made about Ivory's gender identity in the past. I just want to get away from here.
"You're already leaving?" Suddenly, the prince appeared at the door and ignored the loud objections of the royal painter.
"That's not the behavior of a future king!" said Ivory.
"No one will find out. People won't believe you and the painter will keep quiet if his life is worth anything to him." He looked at the painter briefly and then leaned closer to Ivory. "What do you think about a date?" Ivory had been harassed in the past more than once, but never by a prince and especially not by the crown prince.
"Do you actually know what the word 'No' means?" Ivory spat out and pushed the crown prince away from herself.
"No," answered Aquilo with a smile. Of course, the crown prince, who can have anything he wants, doesn't know what the word "No" means.
Ivory rolled her eyes. "Why do you want to go out with someone like me? You must have around 100 admirers?"
"Actually, it's 50," he interrupted Ivory, still smiling. He tossed his hair back, which swirled around in the cold air.
"Come on, get it! Why me? I'm a danger to the palace." Ivory crossed her arms.
"You are the most beautiful girl I have ever seen." Aquilo lifted Ivory's chin with his finger and forced her to look at him.
